Figure 1A

Chronic infections with S. marcescens provided protection against mortality following secondary infection with P. rettgeri

Graph

Mortality following secondary infection with P. rettgeri in flies chronically infected with S. marcescens versus control flies not given a chronic infection. Flies chronically infected with S. marcescens were more likely to survive various doses of secondary infection with P. rettgeri (p < 0.0001).

Chronic infections with E. faecalis provided protection against mortality following secondary infection with P. rettgeri

Graph

Mortality following secondary infection with P. rettgeri in flies chronically infected with S. marcescens versus control flies not given a chronic infection. Flies chronically infected with S. marcescens were more likely to survive various doses of secondary infection with P. rettgeri (p < 0.0001).

#SURVIVAL STATISTICS
#Generate a Cox proportional Hazards model which assesses the contribution of infectious dose while controlling for replicate
E.fae_P.rett$secondary_dose <- as.factor(E.fae_P.rett$secondary_dose)
E.fae_P.rett_coxph <- coxph(Surv(day, status) ~ secondary_dose + primary + rep + primary:secondary_dose + rep:secondary_dose + rep:primary, data = E.fae_P.rett)
#summary(E.fae_P.rett_coxph)
anova(E.fae_P.rett_coxph)
